<%= render 'partials/navbar-dark' %>

<main>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="work">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
          <h1 class="work__header">Some of our work</h1>

          <div class="col-xs-offset-0 col-xs-12 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-12 col-md-offset-2 col-md-8 col-lg-offset-2 col-lg-8">
            <div class="iphone">
              <div class="iphone__image">
                <%= image_tag 'iphone.png', class: 'iphone__img' %>
              </div>
              <div class="iphone__content">
                <h2 class="iphone__title">Let's Go Ride</h2>
                <p class="iphone__description">Let'Go Ride is a cycling app designed with simplicity in mind. It was developed with a focus on a small set of metrics that the average rider is most concerned with, such as distance, time, speed, average speed, and elevation gained.</p>
                <%= link_to image_tag('app_store.png', class: 'app_store'), 'https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/lets-go-ride/id1226006817?mt=8' %>
                <p class="web__tech"><span>Technology:</span> iOS, Swift</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>



          <div class="col-xs-offset-0 col-xs-12 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-12 col-md-offset-0 col-md-12 col-lg-offset-1 col-lg-10">

            <div class="web_top">
              <div class="web__display">
                <%= image_tag 'iam_sample.png', class: 'web__img' %>
              </div>
              <div class="web__content">
                <h2 class="web__title">I Am Worship Church</h2>
                <p class="web__description">I Am Worship Church is a church plant that desired a site that would engage potential visitors when they visited the site. To achieve this we designed a landing page that delivered all essential content, and provided clear navigation to additional content that may be of interest. We also wanted to make sure that current attendees could access the site quickly and easily for important information.</p>
                <p class="web__link"><%= link_to 'View Website', 'http://iamworshipchurch.com', class: 'web__link-a' %></p>
                <p class="web__tech"><span>Technology:</span> Wordpress, Twitter Bootstrap</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="web_alt">
              <div class="web__display">
                <%= image_tag 'untie_sample.png', class: 'web__img' %>
              </div>
              <div class="web_alt__content">
                <h2 class="web__title">Chadwick and Tignor</h2>
                <p class="web__description">Client was seeking a dynamic site that onboard potential clients for packaged services. We achieved this by providing a site where the user was easily and clearly guided through the process of seeking counsel.</p>
                <p class="web__link"><%= link_to 'View Website', 'http://untietheknottn.com', class: 'web__link-a' %></p>
                <p class="web__tech"><span>Technology:</span> Ruby on Rails, Twitter Bootstrap</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="web_bottom">
              <div class="web__display">
                <%= image_tag 'mercy_sample.png', class: 'web__img' %>
              </div>
              <div class="web__content">
                <h2 class="web__title">Mercy Fellowship</h2>
                <p class="web__description">Mercy Fellowship is a church plant that desired a site that would appeal to prospects in a very down to earth, low-key way, but with theological truth. This site was developed in Wordpress to allow them to have control over the content of the site.</p>
                <p class="web__link"><%= link_to 'View Website', 'http://mercynashville.org', class: 'web__link-a' %></p>
                <p class="web__tech"><span>Technology:</span> Wordpress, Twitter Bootstrap</p>
              </div>
            </div>




          </div>



          <!-- <%= image_tag 'mercy_sample.png', class: 'web' %>
          <%= image_tag 'untie_sample.png', class: 'web' %> -->


        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>

<%= render 'partials/footer' %>
